arStrings.szText: You know the Scar, where that demon was killed? Name escapes me. My brother killed a brute there and has been wearing its horn around his neck. “Seven feet tall! It breathed fire! Ma would be so proud!”
Ewan is a happy, excitable drunk, but still coherent. The section in quotes is him mockingly quoting his brothers bragging.
I got sick of the gloating. Insulted his horn’s size. Now we have this wager. I must get a bigger one. Heh, you can see how it’s going.
Say! We’re friends, right? How 'bout you get me a horn, and I’ll give you the coin for the wager. Remember, a really big one!
